Either use one variable e.g. `&lt;xsl:variable name=&quot;items&quot; select=&quot;tokenize($stringToSplit, &#39;#&#39;)&quot;/&gt;` and then `&lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;$items[1]&quot;/&gt;` and `&lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;$items[2]&quot;/&gt;` or set up three variables, the second and third based on the one I have already shown, i.e. `&lt;xsl:variable name=&quot;item1&quot; select=&quot;$items[1]&quot;/&gt;` and `&lt;xsl:variable name=&quot;item2&quot; select=&quot;$items[2]&quot;/&gt;`.

As already pointed out in a comment, your sample, with the suggestions made above, would look like

    &lt;xsl:stylesheet version=&quot;2.0&quot; xmlns:xsl=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform&quot;&gt;
        &lt;xsl:output method=&quot;xml&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot; indent=&quot;yes&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;/&quot;&gt;
            &lt;xsl:variable name=&quot;stringToSplit2&quot; select=&quot;stringToSplit&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;xsl:variable name=&quot;items&quot; select=&quot;tokenize($stringToSplit2, &#39;#&#39;)&quot;/&gt; 
    
            &lt;stringToSplit&gt; 
                &lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;stringToSplit&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;/stringToSplit&gt;
    
            &lt;areaCode&gt; 
                &lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;$items[1]&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;/areaCode&gt;
            &lt;pNumber&gt; 
                &lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;$items[2]&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;/pNumber&gt;
    
        &lt;/xsl:template&gt;
    &lt;/xsl:stylesheet&gt;


https://xsltfiddle.liberty-development.net/3NSSEuT

As I mentioned in a comment to your question, with only two values the simple solution is to use the `substring-before()` and `substring-after()` functions:

**XSLT 1.0**

    &lt;xsl:stylesheet version=&quot;1.0&quot; 
    xmlns:xsl=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform&quot;&gt;
    &lt;xsl:output method=&quot;xml&quot; version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot; indent=&quot;yes&quot;/&gt;
    
    &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;/&quot;&gt;
    	&lt;result&gt;
    		&lt;areaCode&gt; 
    			&lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;substring-before(stringToSplit, &#39;#&#39;)&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;/areaCode&gt;
            &lt;pNumber&gt; 
    			&lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;substring-after(stringToSplit, &#39;#&#39;)&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;/pNumber&gt;
    	&lt;/result&gt;
    &lt;/xsl:template&gt;
    
    &lt;/xsl:stylesheet&gt;

---

This is not only simpler, but also works in XSLT 1.0 (which apparently is the version you&#39;re using): https://xsltfiddle.liberty-development.net/3NSSEuT/1

