If I understand you correctly. You wish to transform a table of non-distinct IDs and associated Values to a table of distinct IDs and a column containing comma-separated values.

If I understand you correctly then I would basically write up a new table. And make a procedure that loops through the first table:

    BEGIN
      FOR cursor IN cursor_through_original_table
        LOOP
        BEGIN
          SELECT value
            INTO temp_variable
            FROM new_table
           WHERE id = cursor.id;
        EXCEPTION
          WHEN no_data_found THEN
            temp_variable := NULL;
        END;
        IF temp_variable IS NOT NULL THEN
          UPDATE new_table
             SET value = temp_variable || &#39;, &#39; || cursor.value
           WHERE id = cursor.id;
        ELSE
          INSERT INTO new_table (id, value)
          VALUES (cursor.id, cursor.value);
        END IF;
      END LOOP;
    END;


This is not code for you to copy-paste, wrote it w/o testing or even rereading it so it&#39;s bound to have errors, and its also missing declarations. But its to get my point across about how to do it.

I hope it fits your needs and you get whatever you are working on working.

